WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'LineBloks' is played on an 8 by 8 tile board, the idea is to
line up 8 tiles of the same pattern in a row or column. When a row
or column is filled with the same type of tiles, those tiles are
removed from the board.

  The game play is simple: move the tiles, by clicking on any tile
on the game board, this will rotate all 8 tiles surrounding it by
one position in a clockwise manner. Any time you move tiles and no
row or column of 8 tiles of the same pattern is created, a new
tile is added on the board. Be careful not to let the board fill
up completely because if that happens, the game is over.

  As the game progress, new tiles with different patterns as well
as 'special' tiles (Bombs, Lightning Tiles, etc.) are added to the
game board.

  Have fun!

